  "text": "Editorial Note: Talk Android may contain affiliate links on some articles. If you make a purchase through these links, we will earn a commission at no extra cost to you. Learn more. Samsung has just unveiled its newest flagship devices, the foldable Z Fold 7 and Z Flip 7. Both devices are a major level up over the previous generation of foldables. In fact, this is the first set of Samsung foldables that I'd actually recommend people buy. The devices are expensive, but the good thing is that as with all big flagship releases, there are more pre-order deals than you can use, and some of them are pretty mouthwatering. Let's dive into what Samsung, Amazon, and the big three carriers have. Image: Samsung Samsung worked hard to make this phone, so there's no better place to stop first than Samsung's own pre-order deals. Whether you're getting the Galaxy Z Fold 7 or the Galaxy Z Flip 7, there are savings to be had if you buy from Samsung's website. Let's start with the star of the show, the Fold: Double the storage for free. The 512GB model is only $1,999, which is the price of the 256GB variant. The 1TB model is discounted $150, bringing its price down to $2,269. Get up to $1,000 off with an eligible trade-in. Without a trade-in, get $300 Samsung credit. Get 10% discounts on the Galaxy Watch 8 series and a 35% discount on the Galaxy Buds 3 Pro. This can be combined with the $300 Samsung credit. Image: Samsung But what if you want the Z Flip 7 instead? The good thing is there are savings to be had there too: Double the storage for free. The 512GB model is only $1,099, which is the price of the 256GB variant. Up to $600 value on an eligible trade-in. Without a trade-in, get $150 Samsung credit. Get 10% off the Watch 8 and Watch 8 Classic, or up to 35% off the Buds 3 series. This can be combined with the $150 Samsung credit. Image: Samsung We can't forget about the new “budget” foldable from Samsung, can we? There are savings to be had there too, though a little less intense. Double the storage for free. You can get the 256GB model for $899, which is the price for the 128GB variant. Get up to $500 off with an eligible trade-in. Without a trade-in, get $100 Samsung credit. Get 10% off the Watch 8 or Watch 8 Classic, and up to 35% off the Buds 3 series. This can be combined with your $100 Samsung credit. Amazon Image: Samsung If you choose to buy Samsung's new foldables straight from Amazon, maybe because it is more convenient, you won't get such a wealth of savings options, but there'll be a gift card included with each new model, and that might be enough. The double storage promotion applies with Amazon too. PhoneAmazon Gift Card ValueSamsung Galaxy Z Fold 7$300Samsung Galaxy Z Flip 7$200Samsung Galaxy Z Flip 7 FE$100 T-Mobile Image: Samsung If you prefer to buy your devices with a carrier, as opposed to unlocked, then T-Mobile has something for you. T-Mobile is the only carrier that will give you double the storage for free, but with some additional perks on top of that. $1,100 off the Z Fold 7 or the Z Flip 7 for free, if you add a line or trade in an eligible device in any condition. However, this applies only to the Experience More, Experience Beyond plans, and their business equivalents. $1,000 off the Z Fold 7 or Z Flip 7 when trading in a device AND adding a line on Business Unlimited Ultimate. $600 off the Z Fold 7 or Z Flip 7 when adding a line on most plans. $500 off when trading in a device on most plans. AT\u0026T Image: Samsung AT\u0026T won't sit around and let T-Mobile get all the spotlight for its deals on the new Samsung foldables. This carrier has some sweet offers too, though it drops some, like the double storage promo. It will give you $1,100 off the Z Fold 7 or the Z Flip 7 for free, as long as you trade in an eligible phone, regardless of the year or condition of the device. It will also give you a special triple bundle offer. When you buy the Z Fold or Flip 7, you will be able to add a Galaxy Watch 8 and a Tab A9+ 5G for only $0.99 each. Verizon Image: Samsung Finally, let's put our sights on the biggest mobile carrier in the US—Verizon. Needless to say, that carrier has deals for you too. $1,100 off the Z Fold 7, or the Z Flip 7 for free, if you're on Unlimited Ultimate and trade-in an eligible device in any condition. Get a free Z Flip 7 (256GB) if you buy a Z Fold/Flip 7 on Unlimited Ultimate or Unlimited Plus. You must open at least one new line, however. $1,000 off the Galaxy Z Fold 7 or Z Flip 7 if you're a Verizon Business customer who signs up for a new line or upgrades. However, requires an eligible trade-in an a My Biz Plan with $20 monthly add-on spending. Verizon will give you six months of Google AI Pro, in addition to the six months Samsung is giving all buyers. Through Tecno, Gionee, Vivo, Google, and now Samsung, Ayomide has always been an Android enthusiast. His current partner in crime is a Samsung Galaxy S22 Ultra. You can find him playing Candy Crush or Call of Duty: Mobile, watching movies, and he is a big fan of trivia and quizzes. Previous Post",
